-- Creative Writing
-- No SQL query can write poetry. The LLM composes, a hard cell counts structure.
-- Poetry requires imagination, cultural awareness, and aesthetic judgment —
-- capabilities that exist only in soft cells.

⊢ topic
  yield subject ≡ "autumn rain on a temple roof"

⊢ compose
  given topic→subject
  yield poem
  ∴ Write a haiku about «subject». Follow the traditional 5-7-5 syllable structure across exactly three lines. Return only the three lines of the haiku, separated by newlines.

⊢ count-words
  given compose→poem
  yield total
  ⊢= sql: SELECT LENGTH(TRIM(p.value_text)) - LENGTH(REPLACE(TRIM(p.value_text), ' ', '')) + 1
     FROM yields p JOIN cells c ON p.cell_id = c.id
     WHERE c.name = 'compose' AND p.field_name = 'poem' AND p.is_frozen = 1

⊢ critique
  given compose→poem
  given count-words→total
  yield review
  ∴ Critique this haiku (word count: «total»):

«poem»

Evaluate: Does it follow 5-7-5 syllable structure? Does the imagery evoke the subject? Is there a seasonal reference (kigo)? Is there a cutting word (kireji) or pause between images? Rate overall quality from 1-5.
  ⊨ review contains at least 2 sentences
